@node Introduction "Introduction to GSEditor"
@next Introduction
@prev Introduction
@{JCENTER}
@{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}
@{JLEFT}
  My first missions on GunShip2000 were terrible; 2 missions and a long distance to go.
  Because I was flying alone, I was shot down very soon. And unless you got promoted to 2LT,
  you still had to fly alone, instead of doing a fast mission with 5 men.
  Somehow I discovered how to change the bits in the roster.dat file and changed it with a Filezapper.
  It was going very well, but I still wasn't satisfied (every time I promoted to BG, I had to load the
  zapper and change it AGAIN :). Then I 쳀inally decided to make an editor for it in AmosPro.
  After about 2 weeks, I started programming this editor in C, from scratch.
  It's now a lot faster, smaller, easier to use and there are more options.

@{JCENTER}And @{i}hastalafiestababy@{ui} here it is.

@{u}@{b}@{i}A GunShip2000 Roster File Editor@{ub}@{ui}@{uu}


@endnode

