@node ToolTypes "ToolTypes"
@next ToolTypes
@prev ToolTypes
@{JCENTER}
@{b}@{u}ToolTypes@{ub}@{uu}
@{JLEFT}
  GSE has as loading default 'DH1:GS2000/roster.dat' and as saving default 'RAM:dumroster.dat'.
  This is done to ensure that the original file isn't overwritten. Better save it to ram:,
  change the original filename and copy the modified file from ram:.
  You can set your own setting by changing the @{b}TOOLTYPES@{ub}.

  @{b} LOADNAME@{ub}  Set a path & filename for loading.
  @{b} SAVENAME@{ub}  Set a path & filename for saving.
    You should ALWAYS give the path and filename.
    Ex: @{i}LOADNAME=DH1:GS2000/roster.dat@{ui}
  @{b} AREA@{ub}  Set the BackFill Area. You can choose from 0 - 2. TRY IT !!! (>8-))
  @{b} SCREENFONT@{ub} Set to TRUE or something else. This is handy if your screenfont
    is larger than 8 or 9 (or crashes), so you don't have to set the prefs to a smaller one.

@endnode

